Residents say there's been no communication or information about where to find water since then. EMFULENI - Emfuleni residents have once again been let down by the municipality. Some areas have been without water since Sunday. READ: Emfuleni Municipality at loggerheads with local businesses Residents say there's been no communication or information about where to find water since then. MMC of Public Works Bheki Ntsele said a statement had been distributed to radio stations and media broadcasters. READ: Vaal River clean-up project stalled again Ntsele said the interruption to the water distribution was initially caused by a power outage and was later exacerbated by low reservoir levels. He named a number of challenges facing the municipality including leakages, poor piping infrastructure, and sanitation problems. Ntsele said the water would likely be restored by Thursday or Friday.